                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#193ra">193ra</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ {ዘደብረማርያም። መካ [sic]} ዘመጽአ፡ እምሀገረ፡ {መካን፡} ምስለ፡ አቡነ፡ መዝገበ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ወዘአውፅኦ፡ እምዝንቱ፡ ደብር፡ ዘሀገረ፡ {ማርያም፡} ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#193ra">193ra</locus>: This (is the) book of Dabra Māryām Mäka(n) which came from the country of Kaswa with ʾabuna Mazgaba Śǝllāse. He who steals it or erases (its text) or takes it out of this church of the country of Māryām shall be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul.</quote>
                           Written in red ink; the hand appears to be the same as the one that executed rubrication. One name is washed out. 
The names connected with the church of Makān Māryām were added in pencil later, replacing the name ካስዋ፡ (an alternative appellation of the monastery of Gunda Gunde) written originally. By substituting the name of Kaswa with the name of Makān the scribe created a contradiction in the note.
ʾAbuna<note> Mazgaba Śǝllāse was the abbot of Gunda Gunde monastery in the second half of the 17th – beginning of the 18th cent.
                        </note>
